The paper proposes a formal framework for a competitive ecosystem where players have the choice to strategize under private payoffs, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of Intention Games in a partially honest setting, which relates to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of content delivery networks and Bitcoin mining, which are topics related to networking (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses a type-theoretic construction of Intention Games, which relates to information theory (cs.IT).
